	Comic Dench    
	 London, Nov. 5 (PTI): Actress Judi Dench and Harry Potter star Maggie Smith are shooting in India for the star studded comedy, The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel.      
	The film is about a group of British pensioners who travel to India to live out their last days. The shooting has started in Rajasthan and the schedule will move next to Bangalore, reports the Daily Mail.      
	Directed by John Madden, the film will also star Slumdog Millionaire actor Dev Patel, Tom Wilkinson and Peter Toole. The sound engineer is Indias award-winning technician Resul Pookutty.    
	Heidi broke     
	Los Angeles (PTI): Reality TV star Heidi Montag and husband Spencer Pratt are considering filing for bankruptcy after spending their $10 million fortune in luxury cars, crystals and Montags 10 plastic surgeries. They owe close to $2 million in taxes. The former stars of The Hills say they have moved into a guesthouse at Pratts parents home after struggling to pay the rent on their $35,000-a-month Malibu mansion.     
	Racing star    
	 London (PTI): Actress Natalie Portman says she likes extreme experiences and loves to go scuba-diving even though she is petrified to undertake any activity that could pose a threat to her life. The Star Wars star enjoys doing things that set her pulse racing. I have fears, Im afraid of a lot. I am not a danger seeker but I do like extreme experiences. But not ones that I feel would threaten my life. I like scuba-diving, for example, but I wouldnt free-dive, said Portman.     
	Miley eye    
	London (PTI): Teen star Miley Cyrus will be seen playing the role of a street-smart private eye in her upcoming action comedy So Undercover. Cyrus, who shot to overnight fame by playing teen star Hannah Montana, has been roped in to play a private eye hired by the FBI to go undercover in a college. The movie, to be directed by Tom Vaughn, goes into production this December with Exclusive Media Group producing and financing the project.     
	Pop fighter    
	 London (PTI): Pop singer Christina Aguilera, who recently filed for divorce from her husband Jordan Bratman, says she is a fighter and tries to thrive when things go out of sync in her life . The singer, who has been a victim of child abuse by her own father, declared that she thrives under duress and has always emerged stronger with every bad experience.                                                                                                                                                       
